.SH NAME
HTMLCanvasElement.webglcontextlost_event \- HTMLCanvasElement:
webglcontextlost event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]webglcontextlost\f[B]\f[R] event of the WebGL API is
fired if the user agent detects that the drawing buffer associated with
a \f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext\f[R] object has been lost.
.PP
This event does not bubble.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\(dqwebglcontextlost\(dq, (event) => { })

onwebglcontextlost = (event) => { }
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A \f[CR]WebGLContextEvent\f[R].
Inherits from \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EVENT PROPERTIES
\f[I]This interface inherits properties from its parent interface,
\f[CI]Event\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]WebGLContextEvent.statusMessage\f[R]
A read\-only property containing additional information about the event.
.SH EXAMPLE
With the help of the \f[CR]WEBGL_lose_context\f[R] extension, you can
simulate the \f[CR]webglcontextlost\f[R] event:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] canvas = document.getElementById(\(dqcanvas\(dq);
\f[B]const\f[R] gl = canvas.getContext(\(dqwebgl\(dq);

canvas.addEventListener(\(dqwebglcontextlost\(dq, (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
  console.log(event);
});

gl.getExtension(\(dqWEBGL_lose_context\(dq).loseContext();

\f[I]// \(dqwebglcontextlost\(dq event is logged.\f[R]
.EE
